.TH "rvt_init_qp" 9 "rvt_init_qp" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
rvt_init_qp \- initialize the QP state to the reset state
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" rvt_init_qp
.BI "(struct rvt_dev_info *rdi "  ","
.BI "struct rvt_qp *qp "  ","
.BI "enum ib_qp_type type "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "rdi" 12
rvt dev struct
.IP "qp" 12
the QP to init or reinit
.IP "type" 12
the QP type
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This function is called from both \fBrvt_create_qp\fP and
\fBrvt_reset_qp\fP.   The difference is that the reset
patch the necessary locks to protect against concurent
access.
